children.text: There are windows that have not been fitted with restrictive devices to prevent openings greater than the allowable 125mm.
Part 3.9.2.6 Protection of openable windows of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘The openable portion of the window must be protected with a device capable of restricting the window opening, and must not permit a 125mm sphere to pass through the window opening or screen’ ;
These windows must be fitted with devices to restrict the openings to 125mm so that they meet the requirements of the BCA.
